   Canadian Steel Ingot Output
</HL>
<DATE>
04/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C5
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel ingot production totaled 272,819
metric tons in the week ended last Saturday, up 7.1% from
254,665 tons in the previous week but down 14% from 317,551
tons a year earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency,
said.
   A metric ton is equal to about 2,204.6 pounds. For this
year through last Saturday, production fell 14% to 4,029,954
metric tons from 4,660,494 tons a year earlier.
